{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Diagnosability change up for review: Gerrit 369 (fix(store): surface git's real stderr on create-path commit failure). event_append.py's create path now includes git's stderr instead of hiding it behind the generic 'git commit failed while holding lock', so the next CI occurrence reveals the true cause (matching the transition path). This is NOT the flake fix — root cause still unconfirmed (not locally reproducible; 0/275 repros + gc hypothesis experimentally refuted). A background flaky-test sweep (6x full suite) is running to try to reproduce it."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783466977770443001,"uuid":"7c7ea4b8-f809-49a1-b932-55157bade0b5"}